 FEATURE n. 1. A surprising property of a program. Occasionally documented.
To call a property a feature sometimes means the author of the program did
not consider the particular case, and the program makes an unexpected,
although not strictly speaking an incorrect response. see BUG. "That's not a
bug, that's a feature!" A bug can be changed to a feature by documenting it.
2. A well-known and beloved property; a facility. Sometimes features are
planned, but are called crocks by others.